In[90]:
# Get unique cities
cities = df["CITY"].unique()

# Create figure
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))

# Plot each city
for city in cities:
    city_data = df[df["CITY"] == city]
    plt.plot(city_data["MONTH"], city_data["AVG_MONTHLY_TEMP_C"],
             marker='o', label=city)

# Labels and title
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Average Monthly Temperature (C)")
plt.title("Monthly Temperature Change for High-Activity Cities in Europe")
plt.xticks(range(1,13))  # ensuring X axis shows months 112
plt.legend(title="City") # creating legend for cities for color defining
plt.grid(True)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Creating a chart for the total snowfall values
# Years to plot
years = ['2019-12', '2020-12', '2022-12', '2023-12', '2025-12']  # adjust depending on your table

# Create figure
x = np.arange(len(df_pivot_snowfall))  # positions for cities
width = 0.15  # width of bars, adjust depending on number of years

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,6))

# Plot bars for each year
for i, year in enumerate(years):
    ax.bar(x + i*width - width*(len(years)-1)/2, df_pivot_snowfall[year], width, label=str(year))

# Labels and title
ax.set_xlabel("City")
ax.set_ylabel("Total Snowfall (cm)")
ax.set_title("Top US Cities with Extreme Total Snowfall per Year (20192025)")
ax.set_xticks(x)
ax.set_xticklabels(df_pivot_snowfall["CITY_NAME"], rotation=45)

# Optional: format Y-axis in thousands if needed
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.FuncFormatter(lambda y, pos: f'{y:,.0f}'))

ax.legend(title="Year")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Create figure
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))

# Setting color palette based on storm score
colors = [
    "darkred" if score > 10.10
    else "firebrick" if score >= 10.00
    else "indianred"
    for score in df["STORM_SCORE"]
]

bars = plt.barh(
    df["CITY_COUNTRY"],
    df["STORM_SCORE"],
    color=colors
)

plt.xlabel("Storm Score")
plt.title("Location with Possible Adverse Weather Conditions Over Next Week")


plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
